00:25:43.338 --> 00:25:44.430
Come on.

259
00:25:55.518 --> 00:25:58.248
There's a guard down at the front gate.

260
00:26:22.712 --> 00:26:23.804
Move.

261
00:26:29.853 --> 00:26:31.081
Come on.

262
00:26:46.237 --> 00:26:47.602
Don't move!

263
00:26:48.105 --> 00:26:50.005
Guns on the ground! Now!

264
00:26:50.675 --> 00:26:53.872
Okay. Okay. just don't shoot.

265
00:26:56.514 --> 00:26:58.210
Turn around! Slowly.

266
00:27:01.653 --> 00:27:03.416
We have them. we have them.

267
00:27:03.989 --> 00:27:05.013
Finish it.

268
00:27:36.623 --> 00:27:39.057
- He took Becky that way.
- Let's go.

269
00:27:44.498 --> 00:27:47.194
- Damn it.
- Sorry. boss. we didn't expect the butcher.

270
00:27:47.768 --> 00:27:50.396
Get everyone over there. Finish it.

271
00:27:56.644 --> 00:27:58.168
Get the kid ready to move.

272
00:28:14.663 --> 00:28:15.823
Becky!

273
00:28:19.367 --> 00:28:21.028
Please. please unlock me.

274
00:28:22.203 --> 00:28:24.263
Becky. the American girl.
Have you seen her?

275
00:28:25.341 --> 00:28:28.105
They took her to another building. I think.

276
00:28:28.311 --> 00:28:31.872
- Where?
- Through tunnels. I can show you.

277
00:28:32.114 --> 00:28:33.945
Please let me go.

278
00:28:34.517 --> 00:28:36.576
- Which way?
- That way.

279
00:28:39.655 --> 00:28:43.056
And now they have Tanya.
Are your guys sleepwalking over there?

280
00:28:43.560 --> 00:28:45.187
They are coming our way
through the tunnels.

281
00:28:45.262 --> 00:28:47.560
Cut them off under Building 3.

282
00:28:47.631 --> 00:28:50.566
And get Tanya back in one piece.
She cost me a fortune.

283
00:29:19.197 --> 00:29:20.494
Look out! Gas!

284
00:29:20.698 --> 00:29:21.687
Get back! Get back!

285
00:29:50.096 --> 00:29:53.156
Pasha. cut them off on the north side of 3.

286
00:29:54.334 --> 00:29:57.633
Gavril. come around from south
in case they head for the gate.

287
00:30:01.074 --> 00:30:02.507
Look. There.

288
00:30:03.777 --> 00:30:05.005
They're on the north side.

289
00:30:05.812 --> 00:30:08.304
They're on the north side of 3.

290
00:30:53.162 --> 00:30:54.686
There are cameras everywhere.

291
00:31:13.884 --> 00:31:15.215
Pull the pin.

292
00:31:15.519 --> 00:31:18.352
On my cue. throw hard.

293
00:31:38.376 --> 00:31:39.365
Now!

294
00:32:03.869 --> 00:32:08.238
Fuck. It's the butcher.
He brought a fucking arsenal.

295
00:32:10.943 --> 00:32:11.932
What?

296
00:32:12.011 --> 00:32:14.139
I hear you're having problems.

297
00:32:15.582 --> 00:32:16.776
I'm handling it.

298
00:32:16.850 --> 00:32:18.545
See that you do.

299
00:32:18.785 --> 00:32:19.774
In an hour.

300
00:32:19.853 --> 00:32:23.755
I'll have no choice but to move in
and shut you down officially.

301
00:32:23.890 --> 00:32:27.348
We have an agreement.
The girl. the Al Khabiri deal...

302
00:32:27.460 --> 00:32:30.054
ls getting less tempting as we speak.

303
00:32:30.130 --> 00:32:33.691
I'm getting some very direct pressure
from the American Embassy.

304
00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:37.066
I've got a police commissioner
nosing around in my business.

305
00:32:37.138 --> 00:32:41.199
All kinds of scrutiny
I spend my life trying to avoid.

306
00:32:41.275 --> 00:32:42.333
I can definitely...

307
00:32:42.410 --> 00:32:46.676
So you have one hour
to make this thing go away.

308
00:32:47.281 --> 00:32:48.771
Or I will.

309
00:32:56.258 --> 00:32:57.623
Fuck!

310
00:32:59.828 --> 00:33:02.388
The girl's ready. Are we moving her?

311
00:33:08.170 --> 00:33:10.331
- Kiril.
- Boss.

312
00:33:12.574 --> 00:33:15.941
Keep blocking the exits.
Pull everyone else back.

313
00:33:16.278 --> 00:33:20.045
Get your brother
and take high positions there and there.

314
00:33:24.087 --> 00:33:26.214
I'm not losing any more men.

315
00:33:29.626 --> 00:33:31.389
Pull back. pull back!

316
00:33:34.497 --> 00:33:36.761
They're pulling back.
Something is going on.

317
00:33:45.542 --> 00:33:48.534
- Hello.
- I'm a businessman first.

318
00:33:48.979 --> 00:33:52.881
This whole mess is getting a bit expensive.

319
00:33:53.884 --> 00:33:55.317
I want to trade.

320
00:33:55.653 --> 00:33:57.951
Your daughter for Tanya.

321
00:34:02.027 --> 00:34:03.324
Let me talk to Becky.

322
00:34:04.195 --> 00:34:06.254
You don't make the rules. Mr. Fayden.

323
00:34:06.665 --> 00:34:07.723
I do.

324
00:34:08.300 --> 00:34:12.031
I'm pulling my men back. and in five
minutes you will walk Tanya out.

325
00:34:12.103 --> 00:34:15.664
and I will do the same with your daughter.
We will trade.

326
00:34:22.848 --> 00:34:24.406
They want to trade.

327
00:34:27.820 --> 00:34:30.414
No. I can't go back.

328
00:34:31.257 --> 00:34:32.246
God.

329
00:34:32.892 --> 00:34:35.986
We can't trust him. It's a setup.

330
00:34:36.896 --> 00:34:38.955
Bring her. Quickly.

331
00:34:51.011 --> 00:34:52.410
In position.

332
00:34:55.248 --> 00:34:56.272
Speaker.

333
00:35:00.420 --> 00:35:01.409
Hello?

334
00:35:02.256 --> 00:35:03.280
No!

335
00:35:03.725 --> 00:35:06.250
That was your daughter's pinky finger.
Mr. Fayden.

336
00:35:06.728 --> 00:35:10.220
If you don't bring Tanya out in four
minutes. I'll start carving her tits.

337
00:35:10.365 --> 00:35:11.627
No!

338
00:35:12.066 --> 00:35:14.227
Oh. and one more thing.

339
00:35:15.103 --> 00:35:18.732
Six meters from where you're hiding.
there is a security camera.

340
00:35:20.108 --> 00:35:24.273
Move the butcher there so I can see him.
or else we don't have a deal.

341
00:35:26.749 --> 00:35:30.810
- What can we do?
- Well. we can't just...

342
00:35:32.588 --> 00:35:35.648
We can't just what?

343
00:35:37.259 --> 00:35:41.389
We can't just what?
They're torturing my baby!

344
00:35:43.265 --> 00:35:44.289
Please.

345
00:35:45.468 --> 00:35:46.594
Please.

346
00:35:49.139 --> 00:35:52.302
I'm sorry. Becky's only 14.

347
00:35:55.745 --> 00:35:57.076
My sister.

348
00:35:58.248 --> 00:36:01.240
My little sister Katya.

349
00:36:03.920 --> 00:36:05.786
She was only 12.

350
00:36:06.524 --> 00:36:08.151
She's the one

351
00:36:10.594 --> 00:36:11.720
they cut up

352
00:36:12.463 --> 00:36:15.193
to make it look like your daughter died.

353
00:36:16.434 --> 00:36:19.062
She did nothing wrong.

354
00:36:19.603 --> 00:36:23.596
She was just the right size. Right hair.

355
00:36:26.912 --> 00:36:27.901
What do we do?

356
00:36:30.982 --> 00:36:32.449
They're setting an ambush.

357
00:36:36.955 --> 00:36:38.115
Do you trust me?

358
00:36:51.170 --> 00:36:52.228
In position.

359
00:36:52.438 --> 00:36:54.531
We're both in position.

360
00:37:10.958 --> 00:37:13.358
- Yes?
- We're coming out.

361
00:37:14.161 --> 00:37:15.253
Good.

362
00:37:23.704 --> 00:37:27.333
One wrong move. and your parents die.
Got it?

363
00:39:10.682 --> 00:39:12.047
Stop.

364
00:39:17.490 --> 00:39:18.684
Switch.

365
00:39:28.234 --> 00:39:29.223
Now!

366
00:39:35.541 --> 00:39:36.702
Take them out.

367
00:39:37.778 --> 00:39:39.268
Take them out.

368
00:39:40.414 --> 00:39:42.382
Take them out now!

369
00:39:42.449 --> 00:39:43.643
Kiril.

370
00:39:44.218 --> 00:39:46.482
Kiril! Gavril!

371
00:39:47.321 --> 00:39:48.515
Gavril!

372
00:39:49.256 --> 00:39:50.621
They're both dead.

373
00:39:52.326 --> 00:39:54.590
Now at this point.
you may be asking yourself

374
00:39:55.162 --> 00:39:58.599
how a man can be
in two places at the same time.

375
00:39:59.968 --> 00:40:02.266
Now that's a very good question.

376
00:40:03.772 --> 00:40:05.239
I used a device called a cycler.

377
00:40:07.042 --> 00:40:11.103
It loops the same image
over and over again on the video feed.

378
00:40:12.380 --> 00:40:14.780
I've found it useful in the past.

379
00:40:21.157 --> 00:40:23.955
Everyone move in.
Take out the kid and the parents. Move in!

380
00:40:24.427 --> 00:40:25.826
Move in now!

381
00:40:46.450 --> 00:40:48.441
Police! Get down. get down!

382
00:40:54.758 --> 00:40:57.056
Police! Lay down your weapons!

383
00:40:57.327 --> 00:41:00.991
This is the police!
Lay down your weapons. or you will be shot!

384
00:43:06.630 --> 00:43:08.222
- These your guys?
- Yeah.

385
00:43:08.332 --> 00:43:09.959
How did you know?

386
00:43:10.901 --> 00:43:13.665
Yes. sir. Thank you. sir.

387
00:43:14.304 --> 00:43:15.635
Will do.

388
00:43:15.873 --> 00:43:18.137
Thank you. Thank you so much.

389
00:43:18.208 --> 00:43:20.403
Your son was very persuasive.

390
00:43:20.677 --> 00:43:23.441
The ambassador goes hunting
with the police commissioner.

391
00:43:23.580 --> 00:43:27.642
The police commissioner. whose brother
was once interrogated by Stelu himself.

392
00:43:28.920 --> 00:43:30.319
You did good. kid.

393
00:43:34.459 --> 00:43:35.483
Thank you.

394
00:43:36.561 --> 00:43:38.756
I'm just glad you finally
called the police.

395
00:43:56.782 --> 00:43:59.080
Thank you doesn't seem enough.

396
00:43:59.685 --> 00:44:01.516
Maybe next time you'll buy a steak or two.

397
00:44:01.954 --> 00:44:03.819
Maybe when I come back for the fight.

398
00:44:04.790 --> 00:44:05.814
Okay.

399
00:44:07.660 --> 00:44:09.252
Let's get going.

400
00:44:17.904 --> 00:44:19.269
Yeah. well.

401
00:44:21.975 --> 00:44:24.603
Dad. your ghosts.

402
00:44:25.378 --> 00:44:26.640
they still visit?

403
00:44:26.713 --> 00:44:28.180
Not for a while.

404
00:44:28.248 --> 00:44:30.843
At least. not where I'm working.

405
00:45:43.560 --> 00:45:45.994
Forgive me. Father. I have sinned.

406
00:45:46.630 --> 00:45:50.964
It's been quite a while
since my last confession.

407
00:45:52.736 --> 00:45:55.501
I wonder.

408
00:45:57.242 --> 00:46:01.303
does God really forgive
even our worst crimes?

409
00:46:02.480 --> 00:46:03.777
God might.

410
00:46:05.417 --> 00:46:06.645
I won't.

411
